{
  "texts": [
    "Ranges in parentheses indicate 95% CI bootstrapped with 1,000 random samples.",
    "MCMRR, mean cross-modal retrieval rank; BPE, Byte-Pair Encoding.",
    "EchoCLIP is an echocardiography vision-language model trained with 1,032,975 video-text pairs derived from 224,685 echocardiography studies across 99,870 patients across a decade of clinical care (Table 1).",
    "In a self-supervised approach, EchoCLIP is trained on pairs of echocardiogram images (randomly sampled from video frames) and associated clinical report text without direct labeling of clinical interpretations or measurements.",
    "The EchoCLIP model uses a ConvNeXt-Base 26 image encoder and a Byte-Pair Encoding text tokenizer 27."
  ]
}